0040|- [HelpText]
0041|*General information on sucros
0043|*Any Survo session or a part of it can be saved in a special file
0044|*(with extension .TUT) as a sucro by working in the tutorial mode.
0045|*This file can be later activated and it imitates actions normally taken
0046|*by the user.
0047|*A sucro file can be loaded to the edit field (TUTLOAD operation),
0048|*edited and saved back to the sucro file (TUTSAVE operation).
0049|*Then various extra comments, conditional statements, prompts for the
0050|*user and time delays may be inserted, too.
0051|*The sucros in Survo range from small macros to user-defined operations
0052|*and large expert applications.
0054|*Originally, the tutorial mode was planned for making tutorials and
0055|*therefore many technical terms still have 'TUT' as a distinctive part.
