0093|- [HelpText]
0094|*Working in tutorial mode:
0095|*A sucro can be defined at any time when working with the Survo
0096|*Editor. To initiate the process, the keys PREFIX and T are pressed which
0097|*leads to a prompt
0099|*   Sucro functions: S=Start definition, R=Run ?
0101|*appearing on the bottom line. After S has been pressed, another prompt
0103|*   Define a sucro: Name of file ?
0105|*is displayed. The user selects a file name like LESSON1  (.TUT is the
0106|*default extension) and thereafter the original situation on the screen
0107|*(before PREFIX T) is restored.
0108|*After this point all the user's actions (key strokes) will be saved in
0109|*the sucro file LESSON1.TUT until PREFIX T is pressed again and a prompt
0111|*   Sucro functions: E=End of definition, C=Control codes, R=Repeat
0113|*is displayed. By selecting E the sucro file will be closed and the new
0114|*sucro is ready for use. By R the new sucro will be repeated immediately.
0116|*The actions saved in a sucro file are automatically executed
0117|*either by activating the command
0118|*/<name_of_sucro>           ( /LESSON1 , for example)
S   |  <             >
0119|*or by pressing PREFIX T and selecting alternative R=Run.
