0132|- [HelpText]
0133|*A sucro can be written in the edit field by using a special sucro language.
0134|*Below a tiny sucro program has been written an saved by a TUTSAVE command:
0135|*  10 *
0136|*  11 *TUTSAVE YEAR_
0137|*  12 / This sucro inserts a new line and writes the current year on it.
0138|*  13 / Insert new line and move the cursor to the beginning of the line:
0139|a  14 *{ins line}{line start}
0140|*  15 / Write and activate TIME command:
0141|a  16 *TIME{act}
0142|*  17 / Return to the beginning of the line and delete 25 first characters:
0143|a  18 *{line start}{del 25}
0144|*  19 / Current year is obtained and the sucro ends:
0145|a  20 *{end}
0146|*Lines starting by /'s are merely comments. The actual program lines contain
0147|*text to be echoed and written to the edit as such (like TIME on line 16).
0148|*There are also various control words and statements written in braces.
0149|*A good way to learn more about sucro programming is to study existing sucros
0150|*(in directories <Survo>\S and <Survo>\TUT, for example)
S   |                 <     >       <     >
0151|*by using the TUTLOAD command.
