0216|*Automatic recording of waiting times
0217|- [/New]
0219|*When a sucro is created in tutorial mode also waiting times between
0220|*consecutive key strokes can be recorded. Thus when running a sucro
0221|*recorded in that way the rhythmn of the original Survo session will
0222|abe followed automatically. There is no need for additional {wait xx}
0223|*statements in the sucro program.
0224|*To employ this feature one has to activate a sucro command
0225|*/WAITREC ON
0226|*before entering the tutorial mode.
0227|*To turn wait recording off
0228|*/WAITREC OFF
0229|*must be activated. The same things can be done by key stroke combina-
0230|ations {pre}LW and {pre}Lw or in sucro code {waitrec on} and {waitrec off},
0231|*correspondingly.
0232|aAfter /WAITREC ON is activated, TUTLOAD command lists statements like {wait 15}
0233|ain a short form {15}.
